<div id="review_11485424" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/11485424" />
    <a title="Jennifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/735866-jennifer"><img alt="Jennifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1199321263p2/735866.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/11485424?book_show_action=true">Jan 02, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer" href="/user/show/735866-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">philosophy majors</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/735866-jennifer?shelf=truly-atrocious-tripe">truly-atrocious-tripe</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer11485424" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17516549245847319969">I really hated this book. In fact, it is the second worst book I&apos;ve ever read (first being the Voyage of Somebody the Sailor). The story made no sense, and key parts of it were left unexplained (what is RAM? what is The Tradition?). I suppose you might get some philosophical value from it, but I didn&apos;t really think any of it was earth-shattering or even worth a raised eyebrow. The only redeeming quality was that it was short and went quickly.</span>
  <span id="freeText17516549245847319969" style="display:none">I really hated this book. In fact, it is the second worst book I've ever read (first being the Voyage of Somebody the Sailor). The story made no sense, and key parts of it were left unexplained (what is RAM? what is The Tradition?). I suppose you might get some philosophical value from it, but I didn't really think any of it was earth-shattering or even worth a raised eyebrow. The only redeeming quality was that it was short and went quickly.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17516549245847319969" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


