  <span id="freeText17359665733738757626" style="display:none">Well, blame me for thinking this book would be about a pilgrimage of the Camino de Santiago. <br />The whole concept of The Order of the RAM felt weird to me and I couldn’t wait to finish the book and be over with it. Also, the practices of the Tradition seemed a bit useless as they were only providing Coelho momentary peace. If it wasn’t peace it was a frustration at not seeing a meaning in what was asked of him to do.<br />The character of Petrus was at least more interesting than Coelho since he wasn’t very talkative about himsef. It made him somewhat mysterious although we had learned his purpose of being Coelho’s master.<br />In the end, the only bits I enjoyed were the descriptions of Spanish landscapes and villages on this route to Santiago de Compostela.</span>
