          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3148407-darnia?shelf=2016">2016</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1179752871" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6707339281746382366">Demi apa gw nemu buku ini cuma ceban doang???!!<br/><br/>***<br/>Ok, here&apos;s my problem with Coelho&apos;s writing: It was hard for me to decided whether the story fiction or not. Same as <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2331.Mitch_Albom' title='Mitch Albom' rel='nofollow noopener'>Mitch Albom</a>&apos;s books, but put some religion thingy into Coelho&apos;s. This is my third book, I&apos;ve read <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/865.The_Alchemist' title='The Alchemist by Paulo Coelho' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Alchemist</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1426.Warrior_of_the_Light' title='Warrior of the Light by Paulo Coelho' rel='nofollow noopener'>Warrior of the Light</a> (this is one of my fave book) and I think this book is the combination of two books I mentioned above. It was about a journey (the alchemist checked), to be specific: a religion journey (the alche</span>
  <span id="freeText6707339281746382366" style="display:none">Demi apa gw nemu buku ini cuma ceban doang???!!<br /><br />***<br />Ok, here's my problem with Coelho's writing: It was hard for me to decided whether the story fiction or not. Same as <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2331.Mitch_Albom" title="Mitch Albom" rel="nofollow noopener">Mitch Albom</a>'s books, but put some religion thingy into Coelho's. This is my third book, I've read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/865.The_Alchemist" title="The Alchemist by Paulo Coelho" rel="nofollow noopener">The Alchemist</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1426.Warrior_of_the_Light" title="Warrior of the Light by Paulo Coelho" rel="nofollow noopener">Warrior of the Light</a> (this is one of my fave book) and I think this book is the combination of two books I mentioned above. It was about a journey (the alchemist checked), to be specific: a religion journey (the alchemist checked), to found a sword (warrior of the light checked) and defeated our own devils (warrior of the light checked).<br /><br />Since I don't understand about The Pilgrimage in Catholic's way, I quite enjoyed the trainings that Paulus gave to Paulo (our MC named Paulo, that made me think is it the author himself's journey?) and also the setting which placed in Santiago de Compostela in Spain. This is not everybody's favorite book I think, but maybe for some people, the journey could be meaningful.</span>
